<h2>What is Women's Health Massage Therapy?</h2>

<p>
Women's Health Massage Therapy is a specialised form of therapeutic massage designed to support women through the physical changes associated with pregnancy, childbirth, postnatal recovery and other musculoskeletal conditions affecting women. Treatment focuses on relieving muscular tension, improving circulation, reducing pain and promoting relaxation while considering your individual health needs and stage of recovery.
</p>

<p>
Unlike a traditional spa massage, our treatments are delivered within a clinical setting by a specialist Women's Health Physiotherapist. Every appointment begins with a brief assessment to understand your symptoms, medical history and treatment goals before selecting the most appropriate massage techniques for your needs.
</p>

<p>
Massage therapy can be used as a standalone treatment or combined with physiotherapy rehabilitation, helping women recover from pregnancy-related aches and pains, postural changes, postnatal muscle tension and everyday musculoskeletal discomfort. Therapeutic massage is commonly used alongside exercise, education and rehabilitation in physiotherapy practice. :contentReference[oaicite:2]{index=2}
</p>

<h3>Massage therapy may help with:</h3>

<ul>
<li>Pregnancy-related back pain</li>
<li>Pelvic girdle pain (PGP)</li>
<li>Neck and shoulder tension</li>
<li>Hip and buttock pain</li>
<li>Postnatal muscular aches and pains</li>
<li>General muscle tightness and stiffness</li>
<li>Stress and tension</li>
<li>Recovery alongside physiotherapy rehabilitation</li>
</ul>

</section>
