<h2>Pregnancy Massage</h2>

<p>
Pregnancy brings many physical and hormonal changes that can place additional strain on your muscles, joints and posture. As your baby grows, changes in weight distribution, ligament laxity and movement patterns can contribute to back pain, pelvic discomfort, hip pain, neck tension and general muscular fatigue.
</p>

<p>
Our specialist pregnancy massage is carefully adapted to each stage of pregnancy, using comfortable positioning and techniques that prioritise both your comfort and safety. Treatment aims to reduce muscular tension, encourage relaxation and improve your overall wellbeing while helping you manage the physical demands of pregnancy.
</p>

<p>
Every treatment is tailored to your symptoms and individual needs. Where appropriate, massage can also be combined with advice on posture, movement, stretching and physiotherapy exercises to help you achieve longer-lasting relief and support a healthy pregnancy.
</p>

<h3>Pregnancy massage may help:</h3>

<ul>
<li>Reduce pregnancy-related back pain</li>
<li>Ease pelvic girdle discomfort</li>
<li>Relieve neck and shoulder tension</li>
<li>Reduce muscular tightness in the hips and legs</li>
<li>Promote relaxation and reduce stress</li>
<li>Improve comfort during everyday activities</li>
<li>Support better movement throughout pregnancy</li>
</ul>

</section>
