<h2>Postnatal Massage</h2>

<p>
Recovering after childbirth places significant physical demands on your body. Whether you have had a vaginal birth or a Caesarean section, caring for a newborn often involves prolonged feeding positions, lifting, carrying, disturbed sleep and repetitive movements that can contribute to neck, shoulder and back pain.
</p>

<p>
Our postnatal massage therapy is designed to support your recovery by relieving muscular tension, improving mobility and helping you feel more comfortable during the early months of motherhood. Every treatment is adapted to your stage of recovery, symptoms and individual goals.
</p>

<p>
Treatment may also complement your postnatal rehabilitation programme by helping reduce muscle tightness, encouraging relaxation and preparing your body for progressive strengthening exercises where appropriate. Physiotherapy commonly combines manual therapy, exercise and education to support recovery after pregnancy. :contentReference[oaicite:0]{index=0}
</p>

<h3>Postnatal massage may help with:</h3>

<ul>
<li>Neck and shoulder pain from feeding and carrying your baby</li>
<li>Upper and lower back pain</li>
<li>Muscle tension and stiffness</li>
<li>Postural discomfort</li>
<li>General fatigue and muscular aches</li>
<li>Stress and emotional wellbeing</li>
<li>Supporting recovery alongside postnatal physiotherapy</li>
</ul>

</section>
